        <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Raymond Carver was a short-story writer and poet. He was born in Clatskanie, Oregon,
                on May 25, 1938, and grew up in Yakima, Washington. He received his BA degree from
                Humboldt State College in 1963 after becoming interested in writing following a
                creative-writing course taught by John Gardner.</p>

        </bioghist>

